# Cloudflare Pages — security headers applied to every response.
#
# CSP notes:
# - script-src is 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' (NO 'unsafe-inline', NO 'unsafe-eval') — every page's
#   JS now lives in its own file (S9: homepage -> /assets/home.js, admin -> /assets/admin.js,
#   changelog -> /assets/changelog.js; the app pages already load external scripts). So an injected
#   inline <script> or onX= handler will not execute, even if markup escaping ever slips.
#   'wasm-unsafe-eval' (owner-approved 2026-07-06) lets the F61a synced-workspaces crypto core
#   COMPILE its Argon2id WebAssembly (hash-wasm inlines the wasm as base64 → WebAssembly.compile,
#   which the default script-src would block). It is WASM-compilation-only: it does NOT re-enable
#   inline/eval JavaScript ('unsafe-inline'/'unsafe-eval' stay absent), so injected JS still can't
#   run. The wasm loads lazily on the cloud-sync path only (dynamic import of core/crypto.ts).
# - style-src is 'self' (NO 'unsafe-inline') — S18/A55 is DONE. There is no inline <style> block
#   and no style="" attribute on any served page: the marketing/admin pages' static inline CSS was
#   extracted to linked stylesheets (home.css, admin.css, site.css), and every dynamic style on the
#   Svelte surfaces is now applied via the CSSOM (NOT gated by style-src): the chart swatch/bar
#   colors+widths go through a use:styleProps action that calls element.style.setProperty(), and the
#   export-report iframe injects its CSS via a constructable stylesheet (adoptedStyleSheets) instead
#   of an inline <style>. Vite extracts every Svelte component <style> to a linked .css at build, so
#   the bundled output carries no inline style either. Result: an injected inline <style> or style=""
#   will not apply, hardening against CSS-based exfiltration/UI-redress. (script-src already omits
#   'unsafe-inline', so this is defense-in-depth, not the only line.)
# - No external origins are needed: every fetch is same-origin (/api/*, /data/*, /app/),
#   and per-trade screenshots are data: URLs (hence img-src 'self' data:). No 'unsafe-eval'.
# - A278 (owner-approved 2026-07-08): the in-app Stripe Payment Element needs js.stripe.com
#   (script + Element iframe), hooks.stripe.com (3DS frames), and api.stripe.com (tokenization
#   fetches). That relaxation is PATH-SCOPED below to the two surfaces that render the form —
#   /app/* and /account.html — via `! Content-Security-Policy` + a re-declared policy (the
#   documented Pages override pattern; without the detach, multiple matching rules would send BOTH
#   CSPs and the stricter one wins, blocking Stripe). frame-src gains 'self' alongside the Stripe
#   origins because the app's export-report iframe is same-origin and there was previously no
#   frame-src at all (it inherited default-src 'self'). Every other page keeps the pure-'self'
#   policy — no third-party script can load on the marketing/info surfaces. Link is disabled in the
#   Element so merchant-ui-api.stripe.com is deliberately NOT allowed.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'

# A278: the Payment Element surfaces — the same policy plus the three Stripe origins.
/app/*
  ! Content-Security-Policy
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://js.stripe.com; style-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://api.stripe.com; frame-src 'self' https://js.stripe.com https://hooks.stripe.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'

/account.html
  ! Content-Security-Policy
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://js.stripe.com; style-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://api.stripe.com; frame-src 'self' https://js.stripe.com https://hooks.stripe.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
